[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "ES (PMID:25913400): Through the examination of a fosmid-based reporter construct containing the entire unc-3 locus, as well as ∼10 kb of upstream and downstream cis-regulatory regions, we find that unc-3 is expressed in all three SAB neurons, but not in postsynaptic muscle cells ( Figure 2D; data not shown)." ;
  lego:evidence          :57c82fad00000276 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2016-09-06" ;
  owl:annotatedProperty  obo:BFO_0000050 ;
  owl:annotatedSource    :57c82fad00000258 ;
  owl:annotatedTarget    :57c82fad00000261
] .

[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  lego:evidence          :57c82fad00000269 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2016-09-06" ;
  owl:annotatedProperty  obo:RO_0002233 ;
  owl:annotatedSource    :57c82fad00000265 ;
  owl:annotatedTarget    :57c82fad00000268
] .

obo:GO_0042789  a  owl:Class .

[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "ES (PMID:25913400): This UNC-3 binding motif was defined through previous analysis of both C. elegans UNC-3 and its vertebrate orthologs [ 15 and 16]. We found one COE motif (COE1) less than 3 kb upstream of the start codon of the madd-4A isoform (which encodes the MADD-4L protein), three COE motifs (COE2-4) in the 5′ region of madd-4B, and one COE motif (COE5) in the first intron of the madd-4B isoform (which encodes the MADD-4B protein) ( Figure 3E). In the context of transgenic animals, small regulatory regions upstream of madd-4A that contain the COE1 motif (2,882 or 734 bp) are sufficient to drive expression of a reporter gene in SAB MNs ( Figure 3F; Table S2), and, as expected, expression of these smaller fragments is unc-3 dependent ( Figures 3B and 3F). Mutation of this phylogenetically conserved COE1 motif in the context of a 734-bp fragment (734 bp COE1 MUT) abrogates expression in the SAB neurons, while expression in other head neurons remains unaffected (Figure 3F; Table S2)." ;
  lego:evidence          :57c82fad00000274 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2016-09-06" ;
  owl:annotatedProperty  obo:RO_0002213 ;
  owl:annotatedSource    :57c82fad00000256 ;
  owl:annotatedTarget    :57c82fad00000262
] .

[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "ES (PMID:25913400): This UNC-3 binding motif was defined through previous analysis of both C. elegans UNC-3 and its vertebrate orthologs [ 15 and 16]. We found one COE motif (COE1) less than 3 kb upstream of the start codon of the madd-4A isoform (which encodes the MADD-4L protein), three COE motifs (COE2-4) in the 5′ region of madd-4B, and one COE motif (COE5) in the first intron of the madd-4B isoform (which encodes the MADD-4B protein) ( Figure 3E). In the context of transgenic animals, small regulatory regions upstream of madd-4A that contain the COE1 motif (2,882 or 734 bp) are sufficient to drive expression of a reporter gene in SAB MNs ( Figure 3F; Table S2), and, as expected, expression of these smaller fragments is unc-3 dependent ( Figures 3B and 3F). Mutation of this phylogenetically conserved COE1 motif in the context of a 734-bp fragment (734 bp COE1 MUT) abrogates expression in the SAB neurons, while expression in other head neurons remains unaffected (Figure 3F; Table S2)." ;
  lego:evidence          :57c82fad00000273 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2016-09-06" ;
  owl:annotatedProperty  obo:RO_0002629 ;
  owl:annotatedSource    :57c82fad00000253 ;
  owl:annotatedTarget    :57c82fad00000256
] .

